 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-EXT CRITICAL-1 (from AUDIT_REPORT): Coherence gate not wired into write path — 99%+ of store mutations bypass contradiction prevention. PROBLEM: The coherence gate (coherence.rs, 1,300 LOC, 18 tests) is well-tested library code but architecturally disconnected from the CLI write path. LiveStore::write_tx() calls store.apply_datoms() directly, bypassing both schema validation and coherence checking. The only production caller of transact_with_coherence() is proposal.rs:468. Every CLI command (observe, write assert, task create, harvest, spec create) bypasses coherence checking entirely. JUSTIFICATION: The coherence gate is the system's primary mechanism for preventing contradictions from entering the store. Without it, every other formal guarantee is undermined — the store can accumulate contradictions unchecked, making INV-COHERENCE-* vacuously true (never tested against real transactions). This is a ~20-line fix with the highest ROI of any finding across all four audits. SOLUTION: Wire transact_with_coherence() into LiveStore::write_tx() as a pre-check. If coherence check fails, return error with recovery hint. VERIFICATION: After fix, manually inject a contradictory assertion and verify it is rejected. DEPENDENCIES: Independent. No prerequisites. Should be the FIRST fix applied. Complements F-INV-001 (LIVE view correctness) — both affect store integrity. FINDING SOURCE: AUDIT_REPORT.md Section 2.2 CRITICAL-1, confirmed by FORMAL_SOUNDNESS_AUDIT_REPORT.md. My FULL_AUDIT missed this entirely. FILES: crates/braid/src/live_store.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/coherence.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/store.rs. SEVERITY: Critical. WAVE: 0. EFFORT: 1h."
